entries.title: Arizona GOP chair: DOJ has not attempted to enforce false-elector subpoenas
entries.description: The batch of subpoenas was one of the earliest public signs of DOJ’s rapidly unfolding criminal investigation related to Trump’s effort to remain in power.

entries.title: Giorgia Meloni's Hard Right Playbook
entries.description: POLITICO Europe’s Hannah Roberts dissects right-wing Italian politics and the rise of Giorgia Meloni, the firebrand politician poised to be Italy’s first female Prime Minister.

entries.title: Georgia and Nevada on their minds: Senate watchers sweat two swing states
entries.description: It’s a tale of four Democratic incumbents. And the two from Arizona and New Hampshire are breathing easier than Raphael Warnock and Catherine Cortez Masto.

entries.title: The nation’s cartoonists on the week in politics
entries.description: Every week political cartoonists throughout the country and across the political spectrum apply their ink-stained skills to capture the foibles, memes, hypocrisies and other head-slapping events in the world of politics. The fruits of these labors are hundreds of cartoons that entertain and enrage readers of all political stripes. Here's an offering of the best of this week's crop, picked fresh off the Toonosphere. Edited by Matt Wuerker.
